    "Short Description": "Wing Guan, founder of Color Matrix, makes it his mission to provide his customers with unique, individualized hairstyles that bring out their personality. Wing cultivated his technique and artistry over 14 years of extensive training and experience, applying the same dedication and rigor to hairstyling that he once did to gymnastics as a national-level athlete. A man of many talents, Wing also operates a cafe at the front of the shop ‚Äî and often treats his salon customers to a free drink!",
    "Image URLs": "{https://storage.googleapis.com/sendchinatownlove-assets/public/assets/color-matrix-cafe-salon/color-matrix-cafesalon-gallery-1.jpg,https://storage.googleapis.com/sendchinatownlove-assets/public/assets/color-matrix-cafe-salon/color-matrix-cafesalon-gallery-2.jpg,https://storage.googleapis.com/sendchinatownlove-assets/public/assets/color-matrix-cafe-salon/color-matrix-cafesalon-gallery-3.jpg}",
    "Story": "Wing Guan first immigrated to the United States 17 years ago. He began working in the hairdressing business, and over the years slowly worked his way up to owning his own salon.\n\nHe learned to cut hair at Wuming Fa (now Tease salon), then spent 3 years perfecting his skills at Subimage in Chinatown. He loves coloring hair, and keeps up with all the latest beauty trends to maintain his self-taught coloring skills.\n\nGuan was finally able to open his own place in 2017 - he is now both the founder and leading stylist of Color Matrix Caf√©Salon in the heart of Chinatown. As an innovative fashionista with an artistic soul, Guan wanted to build a unique sense of community and comfort within his salon. As a result, Color Matrix features a cafe in the front, where customers can enjoy a drink (usually bubble tea!) while waiting for a cut, or just for fun. Not only did Guan design the cafe himself - he hand-built and painted all the furniture.\n\nIn September of 2020, a fire broke out on Grand Street, inflicting heavy damage onto Color Matrix Caf√©Salon and forcing the business to shut down. Guan pulled from whatever he had left in his own savings to cover the losses, but is still in debt from the resulting damage. As he runs the salon himself, Guan had to clean nonstop for 3 days.\n\nA true Renaissance man - national gymnast, furniture maker, cafe owner and of course, lover of all things hairstyling - Guan is emblematic of a Chinatown small business owner using his creative flair to not only offer services but to also build community in the neighborhood.\n\nColor Matrix Caf√©Salon is the first collaborative merchant launch between Welcome to Chinatown and Send Chinatown Love. As our teams continue to serve Chinatown's small business community, we look forward to joining forces for future campaigns to come.",
