    "Short Description": "Melonpanna Tea & Shot is not your traditional 7th Avenue bakery. Since 2018, Ivy has been operating Melonpanna Tea & Shot, bringing the Sunset Park community fresh offerings of homemade sweets and rice dishes. Whether you‚Äôre craving dim sum or on the hunt for a fancy  birthday cake, Melonpanna Tea & Shot has what you‚Äôre looking for and more.",
    "Image URLs": "{https://storage.googleapis.com/sendchinatownlove-assets/public/assets/melonpanna-tea-and-shot/melonpanna-tea-and-shot-gallery-1.jpg,https://storage.googleapis.com/sendchinatownlove-assets/public/assets/melonpanna-tea-and-shot/melonpanna-tea-and-shot-gallery-2.jpg,https://storage.googleapis.com/sendchinatownlove-assets/public/assets/melonpanna-tea-and-shot/melonpanna-tea-and-shot-gallery-3.jpg}",
    "Story": "Ivy, the owner and visionary behind Melonpanna Tea & Shot, wasn‚Äôt always in the restaurant business. After immigrating to America at the age of 13, she went on to pursue a nursing degree and then worked for her family‚Äôs company. Baking, however, had always been a passion for her. As she took a look around Sunset‚Äôs Park‚Äôs Chinese bakery scene, Ivy knew that she could bring something new to the community. This is when she opened Melonpanna Tea & Shot and turned her passion for baking into her American Dream. \n\nSince 2018, Ivy‚Äôs mission for Melonpanna Tea & Shot has always been to bring fun and exciting food items to spark happiness for her community members. When asked about her reason for opening a bakery, she says: ‚ÄúI opened the bakery because I like to look at beautiful things and I like to make people happy.‚Äù After diving deeper into the menu, one can see that baked goods are just the tip of the iceberg. ‚ÄúWe also sell dim sum because I love dim sum. It‚Äôs a time to have everyone from the family together and talk over tea,‚Äù she says, while pointing to the extensive list of dim sum and rice dishes available for customers. ‚ÄúI want to bring everything from my mind into reality.‚Äù\n\nServing joy to the neighborhood through unique cuisine is at the heart of what Ivy does. Since April 24, Ivy and her husband have partially reopened the bakery & caf√© for takeout and delivery, but the road to fully recovering her business from the pandemic‚Äôs impact is still long. Help us keep Ivy‚Äôs dream a reality with a donation or gift card purchase to Melonpanna Tea & Shot!",
