    "Short Description": "Sporting a dark green awning emblazoned with bright white letters, Sun‚Äôs Organic Garden Chinatown (SOGC) has been a cheerful staple of the Bayard Street business block since 2010. Inside this tea lover‚Äôs oasis are rows upon rows of organic teas and herbs ranging from classic teas like Green and Pu‚Äôerh (some dating back to the 1970s) - to rarer finds like Himalayan Shilajit, Wild Blue Lotus flowers, and Yunnan Black Tea from wild ancient trees over 500+ years old. Natalie, SOGC‚Äôs owner (aka the #chinatowntealady) also readily dispenses her wealth of tea and wellness knowledge, ensuring each customer enjoys each cup to the last drop.",
    "Image URLs": "",
    "Story": "For Natalie, SOGC was an embodiment of her dream to serve her community with alternative practical and affordable healthy advice after struggling with her own recovery post 9/11. She discovered the charming spot, resembling a shop right out of Diagon Alley, while shopping in Chinatown, when an ‚ÄúORGANIC TEA‚Äù sign caught her eye in 2016. Organic tea was a rarity in Chinatown, and after trying the loose leaf teas & herbal formulas, she knew she had discovered something great. Fast forward to 2019, her dream was realized when the former owner of Sun‚Äôs retired and passed on the torch of becoming the shop‚Äôs owner, tea sommelier and wellness guru to her. \n\nMore than just a tea shop, Sun‚Äôs is a calming oasis among the hustle and bustle of NY Chinatown. Natalie‚Äôs customers trust her to recommend the right tea or herb for every flavor palate & need, curated from only reputable vendors in China, Taiwan, India, Africa and the rest of the world. For the elderly population and ethnic community of Chinatown and Manhattan, it is an essential and beloved local shop to get quality tea and health-boosting and anti-aging herbs. SOGC also offers a holistic and non-Western approach towards wellness that is rooted in both tradition & science - one that is much needed and often lacking in New York. Customers everywhere come for the quality products but experience much more than that ‚∏∫ they leave enriched and more knowledgeable about both Chinese tea culture and holistic wellness.\n\n2020 has presented unique challenges for SOGC. Earlier in 2020, a large fire on Bayard Street blocked off most of the street, eliminating cars and cutting down foot traffic. With COVID-19, tourism and local traffic was further reduced for not only Natalie‚Äôs shop, but also the surrounding Bayard Street businesses. Currently, Natalie can only afford to operate the store 2 days a week.\n\nAs the sole employee of the shop, Natalie remains dedicated to keeping the store open to serve the greater community by giving them access to Chinese tea culture and its rich heritage, and to offer affordable holistic solutions to people‚Äôs health issues. Just a glance at SOGC‚Äôs Google & Yelp reviews show just how much her customers value & appreciate her help & service. Let‚Äôs keep Natalie‚Äôs mission alive and this happy tea shop open. Help Sun‚Äôs Organic Garden Chinatown by donating today.",
