    "Short Description": "Founded in 2019, Yue Wong Restaurant on Bayard Street serves delicious Cantonese and Hong Kong style food. Their barbecued meats such as roast pork, soy sauce chicken and roast duck attract a loyal clientele of locals and tourists alike, fulfilling Mr. Chan‚Äôs passion for cooking and bringing good food to Chinatown.",
    "Image URLs": "{https://storage.googleapis.com/sendchinatownlove-assets/public/assets/yue-wong-restaurant/yue-wong-restaurant-1.jpg,https://storage.googleapis.com/sendchinatownlove-assets/public/assets/yue-wong-restaurant/yue-wong-restaurant-2.jpg,https://storage.googleapis.com/sendchinatownlove-assets/public/assets/yue-wong-restaurant/yue-wong-restaurant-3.jpg,https://storage.googleapis.com/sendchinatownlove-assets/public/assets/yue-wong-restaurant/yue-wong-restaurant-4.jpg}",
    "Story": "For Mr. Chan, cooking runs in the family. Mr. Chan‚Äôs parents are chefs who immigrated to the United States a few years ahead of him. While his parents settled into New York City, Mr. Chan perfected his craft at large restaurants and hotels in Shenzhen. Eventually they were able to sponsor Mr. Chan to immigrate to the US in 2014, and help open Yue Wong.\n\nWith reduced foot traffic in Chinatown and Covid-19 concerns, paying bills and keeping his employees safe has been harder than ever. Mr. Chan is most concerned for his 9 dedicated team members, who have been his close friends and confidants prior to Yue Wong. The implications of closing are dire - not only would it impact his life, but would also impact the lives of some of his dearest friends and the Chinatown community as a whole. That‚Äôs a reality that weighs on him everyday.\n\nDuring these uncertain times, Mr. Chan has managed to adapt by reducing the menu to only serving popular items like barbecued meats. He plans to expand the menu to include classic Chinese dishes in the long term, a sign of hope for the future of the restaurant.\n\nLet‚Äôs help Mr. Chan preserve his lifelong dream to make delicious food while supporting his staff and community around him, whose needs he has always kept in the forefront of his mind during the pandemic.",
